From d1121decafb6e941839d8780f1c81dc49149d27b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Zomba <izomba-lang@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 00:38:14 +0400
Subject: [PATCH] fix: non-blocking startup + coerce numeric tool params

- Warm entity cache in a background task and swallow FloodWaitError so a
  Telegram rate-limit at startup no longer blocks the MCP handshake (the
  client was dropping the server). Also route startup logs to stderr - on a
  stdio MCP server stdout is the JSON-RPC channel.
- Accept Union[int, str] for numeric tool params (page/page_size/limit/etc)
  and coerce via int(), so clients passing numbers as strings don't error.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
